
Project Overview

SchedulingPro is a beginner-friendly Python and Flask web application designed to simulate a scheduling platform for veterans filing VA disability claims.

The app allows users to:
- Select a VA disability claim type
- Find nearby contracted clinics
- Filter clinics by distance or earliest availability
- Choose an appointment time
- Review appointment details
- Receive a confirmation number

This project was built as a learning project to practice:
- Python fundamentals
- Flask web development
- HTML/CSS rendering in Flask
- Routing and query parameters
- Lists and dictionaries
- Sorting/filtering logic
- User workflow design
- Healthcare scheduling concepts

The current version uses mock/demo data and does not connect to real VA systems or GPS services yet.

Application Workflow

1. Home Page
The user selects their claim type.

2. Location Page
The user clicks “Use my location” to simulate location services.

3. Results Page
The application filters and displays matching clinics.

4. Review Page
The user reviews their appointment details.

5. Confirmation Page
The app generates a random confirmation number and confirms the booking.

Technologies Used
- Python
- Flask
- HTML
- CSS
- Random module

How to Run the Project

Step 1 — Install Python
Download Python from:
https://www.python.org/downloads/

Step 2 — Install Flask
Run:
pip install flask

Step 3 — Run the Application
Run:
python app.py

Step 4 — Open in Browser
Open:
http://127.0.0.1:5000

Current Features
- Claim selection
- Clinic filtering
- Appointment selection
- Distance sorting
- Soonest appointment sorting
